name: Articuno
flavorText: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Articuno from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Cresselia
flavorText: Shiny particles are released from its wings like a veil. It is said to represent the crescent moon.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.
Attack2Text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Darkrai from your hand onto your Bench, you may choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon. That Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack1Text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon is Asleep, remove 4 damage counters from Darkrai.

name: Dialga
Attack1Text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Glaceon
flavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Glaceon during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance, Poké-Powers, Poké-Bodies, or any other effects on the Defending Pokémon.

name: Kabutops
flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.
Ability1Text: As long as Kabutops is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Trainer cards from his or her hand.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Leafeon
flavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Leafeon by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Manaphy
flavorText: Born on a cold seafloor, it will swim great distances to return to its birthplace.
Ability1Text: When you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Manaphy, remove 2 damage counters from Manaphy.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for any 1 card and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: You may attach up to 2 basic Water Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like.

name: Mewtwo
flavorText: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew's genes. It's said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 Energy cards and attach them to Mewtwo.
Attack2Text: Discard a Psychic Energy attached to Mewtwo and remove 6 damage counters from Mewtwo.

name: Moltres
flavorText: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Moltres from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for up to 3 Fire Energy cards and attach them to Moltres.
Attack1Text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Moltres.

name: Palkia
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: You may return an Energy card attached to Palkia to your hand. If you do, choose an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon and return it to your opponent's hand.

name: Phione
flavorText: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from 1 of your Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon. (This counts as evolving that Pokémon.) Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Rotom
flavorText: Its body is composed of plasma. It is known to infiltrate electronic devices and wreak havoc.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Move an Energy card attached to Rotom to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you put Zapdos from your hand onto your Bench, you may flip a coin. If heads, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Does 40 damage to 1 of your Pokémon, and don't apply Weakness and Resistance to this damage.

name: Aerodactyl
flavorText: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.
Ability1Text: After your opponent's Pokémon uses a Poké-Power, put 2 damage counters on that Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Bronzong
flavorText: One caused a news sensation when it was dug up at a construction site after a 2,000-year sleep.
Ability1Text: As long as Bronzong is your Active Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon that has any Poké-Powers between turns.
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon that already has damage counters on it.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done to Bronzong by attacks is reduced by 20 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Empoleon
flavorText: It swims as fast as a jet boat. The edges of its wings are sharp and can slice apart drifting ice.
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to each of them. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Does 50 damage plus 10 more damage for each of your Benched Pokémon. Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Espeon
flavorText: Its fur has the look and feel of velvet. The orb on its forehead glows when it uses psycho-power.
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that evolves from Eevee gets +20 HP. You can't use more than 1 Sunlight Veil Poké-Body each turn.
Attack1Text: You may move an Energy card attached to Espeon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Flareon
flavorText: It has a flame sac in its body. Its body temperature tops 1,650 degrees Fahrenheit before battle.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy card attached to Flareon and then discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Glaceon
flavorText: As a protective technique, it can completely freeze its fur to make its hairs stand like needles.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Hippowdon
flavorText: Its huge mouth is almost seven feet across. It has enough power to completely crush a car.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for a Fighting Energy card and attach it to Hippowdon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin for each Fighting Energy attached to Hippowdon. This attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Infernape
flavorText: Its crown of fire is indicative of its fiery nature. It is beaten by none in terms of quickness.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Discard all Fire Energy attached to Infernape. This attack does 40 damage times the amount of Fire Energy you discarded.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: It controls 10,000-volt power and can raise all the furs on its body as if it were sharp needles.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: You may discard 2 Energy attached to Jolteon. If you do, this attack's base damage is 90 instead of 50.

name: Leafeon
flavorText: Just like a plant, it uses photosynthesis. As a result, it is always enveloped in clear air.
Attack1Text: Remove 1 damage counter from Leafeon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Minun
flavorText: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.
Attack2Text: If Plusle is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Omastar
flavorText: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, when you play Omastar from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may remove the highest Stage Evolution card from each of your opponent's Benched Evolved Pokémon and put those cards back into his or her hand. You can't use more than 1 Primal Swirl Poké-Power each turn.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

name: Phione
flavorText: A Pokémon that lives in warm seas. It inflates the flotation sac on its head to drift and search for food.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, any damage done by attacks from the Defending Pokémon is reduced by 20 (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Plusle
flavorText: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: If Minun is on your Bench, this attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage.

name: Scizor
flavorText: It has a steel-hard body. It intimidates foes by upraising its eye-patterned pincers.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon has any Special Energy cards attached to it, this attack does 30 damage plus 50 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 50 damage plus 40 more damage.

name: Torterra
flavorText: Groups of this Pokémon migrating in search of water have been mistaken for "moving forests."
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Torterra can't use Frenzy Plant during your next turn.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: The toxin made in its poison sacs is pumped to the knuckle claws through tubes down its arms.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned. Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Umbreon
flavorText: The light of the moon changed Eevee's genetic structure. It lurks in darkness for prey.
Ability1Text: Each of your Pokémon that evolves from Eevee has no Weakness, and that Pokémon's Retreat Cost is 0.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Unown [P]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown P is on your Bench, you may put 1 damage counter on 1 of your Pokémon (excluding any Unown).
Attack1Text: Each player discards the top card of his or her deck. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each Unown discarded in this way.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: It has evolved to be suitable for aquatic life. It can invisibly melt away into water.
Attack1Text: Remove 2 damage counters from each of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Ambipom
flavorText: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 card from your opponent's hand without looking. Look at that card you chose, then have your opponent shuffle that card into his or her deck.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Fearow
flavorText: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Grotle
flavorText: The shell is hardened soil. Some Pokémon come to peck the berries growing on the trees on its back.
Attack1Text: Attach a Grass Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Lickitung
flavorText: Instead of hands, it uses its tongue, which is twice its height. Its sticky saliva grips anything.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to Manectric and this attack does 40 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Monferno
flavorText: It uses ceilings and walls to launch aerial attacks. Its fiery tail is but one weapon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Mothim
flavorText: It loves the honey of flowers and steals honey collected by Combee.
Ability1Text: Any damage done by attacks from your Pokémon to the Defending Pokémon isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage times the number of different types of Wormadam on your Bench.
Attack2Text: You may switch Mothim with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, move as many Energy cards attached to Mothim as you like to the new Active Pokémon.

name: Pachirisu
flavorText: It makes electricity with pouches in its cheeks and shoots charges from its tail. It lives atop trees.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for a Lightning Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Prinplup
flavorText: Its wings deliver wicked blows that snap even the thickest of trees. It searches for prey in icy seas.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Raichu
flavorText: It can loose 100,000-volt bursts of electricity, instantly downing foes several times its size.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Raichu during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy cards attached to Raichu.

name: Scyther
flavorText: It is nearly impossible to parry its attacking scythes. Its movements are like a ninja's.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 20 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 40 more damage.

name: Staravia
flavorText: It lives in forests and fields. Squabbles over territory occur when flocks collide.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 30 more damage.

name: Sudowoodo
flavorText: It stands along paths pretending to be a tree. If it starts raining, it seems to disappear.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage times the number of damage counters on Sudowoodo.
Attack2Text: Sudowoodo does 30 damage to itself.

name: Unown [Q]
flavorText: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Unown Q is on your Bench, you may discard all cards attached to Unown Q and attach Unown Q to 1 of your Pokémon as a Pokémon Tool card. As long as Unown Q is attached to a Pokémon, you pay Colorless less to retreat that Pokémon.

name: Aipom
flavorText: It lives atop giant trees. It wraps its tail around a branch so it won't fall off while asleep.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Return Aipom and all cards attached to it to your hand. (If you don't have any Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.)

name: Aipom
flavorText: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Bronzor
flavorText: X-ray photos were taken to check its body structure. Nothing appeared, however.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Buneary
flavorText: When it senses danger, it perks up its ears. On cold nights, it sleeps with its head tucked into its fur.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Energy card, show it to your opponent, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Remove 1 damage counter from each of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Burmy Sandy Cloak
flavorText: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all effects of an attack, including damage, done to Burmy Sandy Cloak during your opponent's next turn.

name: Chatot
flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a number of cards equal to the number of cards in your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Chimchar
flavorText: Its fiery rear end is fueled by gas made in its belly. Even rain can't extinguish the fire.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Chimchar
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

name: Chingling
flavorText: It emits cries by agitating an orb at the back of its throat. It moves with flouncing hops.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Chimecho from your hand onto Chingling (this counts as evolving Chingling) and remove all damage counters from Chingling.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Combee
flavorText: It collects and delivers honey to its colony. At night, they cluster to form a beehive and sleep.
Attack1Text: Remove 2 damage counters from 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: Inflating its poison sacs, it makes an eerie blubbering sound for intimidation.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Drifloon
flavorText: It tugs on the hands of children to steal them away. However, it gets pulled around instead.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put any 1 card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Switch Drifloon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for as many Eevee as you like and put them onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: A rare Pokémon that adapts to harsh environments by taking on different evolutionary forms.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

name: Electrike
flavorText: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Glameow
flavorText: With its sharp glare, it puts foes in a mild hypnotic state. It is a very fickle Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

name: Hippopotas
flavorText: It enshrouds itself with sand to protect itself from germs. It does not enjoy getting wet.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.
Attack2Text: Hippopotas does 10 damage to itself.

name: Kabuto
flavorText: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for Helix Fossil, Dome Fossil, or Old Amber and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward. This power can't be used if Kabuto is affected by a Special Condition.

name: Munchlax
flavorText: It hides food under its long body hair. However, it forgets it has hidden the food.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put Snorlax from your hand onto Munchlax (this counts as evolving Munchlax) and remove all damage counters from Munchlax.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Omanyte
flavorText: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, search your discard pile for Helix Fossil, Dome Fossil, or Old Amber and put it onto your Bench. This power can't be used if Omanyte is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Does 10 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pikachu
flavorText: If it looses crackling power from the electric pouches on its cheeks, it is being wary.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.
Attack2Text: Pikachu does 10 damage to itself.

name: Piplup
flavorText: It lives along shores in northern countries. A skilled swimmer, it dives for over 10 minutes to hunt.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 damage plus 10 more damage.

name: Piplup
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Shellos East Sea
flavorText: It lives along bodies of water. Its body shape changed to suit its habitat.
Attack2Text: Does 10 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Spearow
flavorText: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Starly
flavorText: Usually with a large flock, it is barely noticeable when alone. Its cries are very strident.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches the Defending Pokémon with 1 of his or her Benched Pokémon.

name: Stunky
flavorText: It sprays a nose-curling, stinky fluid from its rear to repel attackers.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Turtwig
flavorText: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Old Amber
Ability1Text: As long as Old Amber is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to Old Amber by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Dome Fossil
Ability1Text: When you attach a Fighting Energy card from your hand to Dome Fossil (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), search your deck for a card that evolves from Dome Fossil and put it onto Dome Fossil (this counts as evolving Dome Fossil). Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Helix Fossil
Ability1Text: When you attach a Water Energy card from your hand to Helix Fossil (excluding effects of attacks or Poké-Powers), search your deck for a card that evolves from Helix Fossil and put it onto Helix Fossil (this counts as evolving Helix Fossil). Shuffle your deck afterward.

name: Garchomp LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Garchomp LV.X from your hand onto your Active Garchomp, you may flip 3 coins. For each heads, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Search your discard pile for a Pokémon (excluding Pokémon LV.X) and put it onto your Bench as a Basic Pokémon. Then, you may search your discard pile for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to that Pokémon.

name: Glaceon LV.X
Ability1Text: As long as Glaceon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent's Pokémon can't use any Poké-Powers.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Leafeon LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon. This power can't be used if Leafeon is affected by a Special Condition.
Attack1Text: Does 30 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to all of your Pokémon.

name: Porygon-Z LV.X
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), when you put Porygon-Z LV.X from your hand onto your Active Porygon-Z, you may discard all of your opponent's Special Energy cards in play.
Ability2Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for up to any 2 cards and shuffle your deck afterward. Then, put those cards on top of your deck in any order. This power can't be used if Porygon-Z is affected by a Special Condition.
